{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>Two well-characterised systems produce polysaccharide based on N-acetyl-D-glucosamine in straight chains with beta-1,6 linkages. These are encoded by the icaADBC operon in Staphylococcus species and the pgaABCD operon in Gram-negative bacteria such as E. coli. Both systems include a putative polysaccharide deacetylase. The PgaB protein, described in this entry, contains an additional domain lacking from its Gram-positive counterpart IcaB ([ncbifam:TIGR03933]).</p>\n\n<p>PgaB catalyses the N-deacetylation of poly-beta-1,6-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine, a biofilm adhesion polysaccharide [[cite:PUB00055021], [cite:PUB00055022]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure {"accession" "6au1", "name" "Structure of the PgaB (BpsB) glycoside hydrolase domain from Bordetella bronchiseptica"}, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"ncbifam" {"TIGR03938" "poly-beta-1,6-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine N-deacetylase PgaB"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Poly-beta-1,6-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine N-deacetylase PgaB", "short" "PGA_deacetylase_PgaB"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 11, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 253, "taxa" 2060, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 2337, "sets" 0, "proteins" 2337, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 1698}, "pathways" 22}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {"gp" {"displayName" "Genome Properties", "description" "Genome properties is an annotation system whereby functional attributes can be assigned to a genome, based on the presence of a defined set of protein signatures within that genome.", "rank" 45, "accessions" [{"accession" "GenProp0907", "url" "https://www.ebi.ac.uk/interpro/genomeproperties/genome-property/GenProp0907"}]}, "ec" {"displayName" "ENZYME", "description" "ENZYME is a repository of information relative to the nomenclature of enzymes. It is primarily based on the recommenda